                "node_class": "AnthropicNode",
                "replies": [
                 {
                  "content": "Good call on simplifying to just insert_after. Let me specify the grammar first and then propose the implementation structure.\n\nGrammar in EBNF-style notation:\n```\nscope ::= file_path \"::\" class_path? \"::\" method_name?\nfile_path ::= [^:]+ \".py\"  # Any non-colon chars ending in .py\nclass_path ::= class_name (\"::\" class_name)*  # Supports nested classes\nclass_name ::= [A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*  # Python class name rules\nmethod_name ::= [A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*  # Python method name rules\n\nExamples:\n\"myfile.py\"  # Target whole file\n\"myfile.py::MyClass\"  # Target class\n\"myfile.py::MyClass::method\"  # Target method\n\"myfile.py::Outer::Inner::method\"  # Target nested method\n```\n\nHere's the proposed function signature with detailed docstring:\n\n```python\ndef python_edit(target_scope: str, code: str, *, insert_after: str = None) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Edit Python code using pytest-style scope syntax.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    ----------\n    target_scope : str\n        Location to edit in pytest-style scope syntax:\n        - \"file.py\" (whole file)\n        - \"file.py::MyClass\" (class)\n        - \"file.py::MyClass::method\" (method)\n        - \"file.py::Outer::Inner::method\" (nested)\n        \n    code : str\n        Python code to insert/replace. Will be cleaned/dedented.\n        Import statements will be automatically extracted and handled.\n        \n    insert_after : str, optional\n        Where to insert the code. Can be either:\n        - \"__FILE_START__\" (special token for file beginning)\n        - A scope (\"MyClass::method\")\n        - An exact line match\n        If not specified, replaces the node at target_scope.\n    \n    Returns:\n    --------\n    str\n        Description of what was modified or error message\n        \n    Examples:\n    --------\n    # Replace class\n    python_edit(\"myfile.py::MyClass\", '''\n        class MyClass:\n            def method(self):\n                pass\n    ''')\n    \n    # Add method to class\n    python_edit(\"myfile.py::MyClass::new_method\", '''\n        def new_method(self):\n            pass\n    ''')\n    \n    # Insert after specific line\n    python_edit(\"myfile.py::MyClass::method\", '''\n        def method(self):\n            pass\n    ''', insert_after=\"# Insert here\")\n    \n    # Insert at file start\n    python_edit(\"myfile.py\", \"import logging\", insert_after=\"__FILE_START__\")\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\nThe implementation would:\n1. Use the same error handling pattern returning strings\n2. Use _clean() for code cleaning/dedenting\n3. Handle imports automatically like current version\n4. Use AST for parsing/modification\n5. Support exact scoping via the pytest syntax\n6. Include detailed error messages for:\n   - Invalid scope syntax\n   - Scope not found\n   - Ambiguous insert_after matches\n   - Parse errors in provided code\n   - File access errors\n\nWould you like me to proceed with implementing this design?",
