                                                                                                                                                                                                      "content": "Looking at the debug output, I see several issues:\n\n1. Line-based insertion is failing because of indentation issues in the reconstructed source. We need to fix how we handle the function source:\n```python\nDEBUG - New source:\n    def another_method(self):\n        # Insert here\n        x = 42\n        pass\n```\nThe extra indentation at the start is causing the \"unexpected indent\" error.\n\n2. Scope-based insertion isn't matching correctly:\n```python\nDEBUG - Scope insertion: target=['OuterClass', 'another_method'], current=OuterClass\n```\nWe're not properly comparing the paths.\n\nLet me fix these issues. First, the line-based insertion:",
