                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "content": "The focused tests reveal several specific issues:\n\n1. Comment Preservation:\n```python\nDEBUG - Body lines: ['    # First comment', '    x = 1', '    # Target comment', '    y = 2']\n# But in result:\ndef my_func():\n    x = 1\n    z = 3\n    y = 2\n```\nWe're losing comments when parsing/reconstructing the AST.\n\n2. Import Handling:\n```python\nDEBUG - Result content:\nx = 1\ny = 2\nz = 3\n```\nImports aren't being processed at all - they're being treated as regular code.\n\n3. Indentation in Class:\n```python\nDEBUG - Scope insertion: target=['MyClass', 'method_one'], current=['MyClass']\n```\nThe scope matching is failing to handle the insert_after case properly.\n\n4. Scope Path Matching:\n```python\nDEBUG - Function node: method at lines 5-5\nDEBUG - Body lines: []\n```\nWe're not correctly handling one-line function definitions.\n\nLet me fix the comment preservation first by modifying how we handle the function body:",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "pending_results": [],
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "role": "assistant",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "tool_calls": [
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               {
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                "type": "tool_use",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                "id": "toolu_01PZb74tNQ66N1iP6Jy5RZnC",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                "name": "add_function_to_class",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                "input": {
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 "file_path": "bots/tools/python_editing_tools.py",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 "class_name": "ScopeTransformer",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 "new_method_def": "\n                            def _get_node_source(self, node):\n                                \"\"\"Get the full source of a node, including comments\"\"\"\n                                if not hasattr(node, 'lineno') or not hasattr(node, 'end_lineno'):\n                                    return _py_ast_to_source(node)\n                                \n                                # Get the raw lines from the file\n                                lines = self.file_lines[node.lineno-1:node.end_lineno]\n                                return '\\n'.join(lines)\n                            \n                            def _get_node_body_source(self, node):\n                                \"\"\"Get the body source of a node, including comments\"\"\"\n                                if not hasattr(node, 'lineno') or not hasattr(node, 'end_lineno'):\n                                    return _py_ast_to_source(node)\n                                    \n                                # Get all lines except the definition line\n                                lines = self.file_lines[node.lineno:node.end_lineno]\n                                if not lines:\n                                    return \"\"\n                                    \n                                # Find base indentation from first non-empty line\n                                base_indent = 0\n                                for line in lines:\n                                    if line.strip():\n                                        base_indent = len(line) - len(line.lstrip())\n                                        break\n                                        \n                                # Remove base indentation from all lines\n                                return '\\n'.join(\n                                    line[base_indent:] if line.strip() else ''\n                                    for line in lines\n                                )\n                            \n                            def _handle_insertion(self, node):\n                                \"\"\"Handle inserting nodes after a specific point.\"\"\"\n                                if isinstance(self.insert_after, str) and '::' not in self.insert_after:\n                                    # Line-based insertion\n                                    if isinstance(node, (ast.FunctionDef, ast.AsyncFunctionDef)):\n                                        print(f\"\\nDEBUG - Function node: {node.name}\")\n                                        \n                                        # Get the function's body with comments\n                                        body_source = self._get_node_body_source(node)\n                                        body_lines = body_source.split('\\n')\n                                        print(f\"DEBUG - Body source:\\n{body_source}\")\n                                        \n                                        # Find the line and its indentation\n                                        target = self.insert_after.strip()\n                                        print(f\"DEBUG - Looking for target: '{target}'\")\n                                        \n                                        for i, line in enumerate(body_lines):\n                                            line = line.rstrip()\n                                            print(f\"DEBUG - Checking line: '{line}'\")\n                                            if line.strip() == target:\n                                                print(f\"DEBUG - Found match at line {i}\")\n                                                self.line_match_count += 1\n                                                if self.line_match_count == 1:\n                                                    # Get base indentation from the matching line\n                                                    base_indent = len(line) - len(line.lstrip())\n                                                    print(f\"DEBUG - Base indent: {base_indent}\")\n                                                    \n                                                    # Insert new nodes with matching indentation\n                                                    insertion = []\n                                                    for new_node in self.new_nodes:\n                                                        node_lines = _py_ast_to_source(new_node).split('\\n')\n                                                        for nl in node_lines:\n                                                            if nl.strip():\n                                                                insertion.append(' ' * base_indent + nl.lstrip())\n                                                            else:\n                                                                insertion.append('')\n                                                    print(f\"DEBUG - Insertion lines: {insertion}\")\n                                                    \n                                                    # Insert after the matching line\n                                                    body_lines[i:i+1] = [body_lines[i]] + insertion\n                                                    self.success = True\n                                                    break\n                                        \n                                        if self.line_match_count == 0:\n                                            print(\"DEBUG - No matches found\")\n                                            return node\n                                        elif self.line_match_count > 1:\n                                            raise ValueError(f\"Ambiguous insert_after - found {self.line_match_count} matches for: {self.insert_after}\")\n                                        \n                                        # Reconstruct the function with the modified body\n                                        func_def = self._get_node_source(node).split('\\n')[0]  # Get function definition line\n                                        new_source = func_def + '\\n' + '\\n'.join(body_lines)\n                                        print(f\"DEBUG - New source:\\n{new_source}\")\n                                        \n                                        try:\n                                            new_node = ast.parse(new_source).body[0]\n                                            return new_node\n                                        except Exception as e:\n                                            print(f\"DEBUG - Parse error: {str(e)}\")\n                                            return node\n                                else:\n                                    # Scope-based insertion\n                                    if self.insert_after:\n                                        target_path = self.insert_after.split('::')\n                                        current_path = self.current_path\n                                        print(f\"DEBUG - Scope insertion: target={target_path}, current={current_path}\")\n                                        \n                                        # Check if we're at the target scope\n                                        if target_path == current_path:\n                                            self.success = True\n                                            if isinstance(node, ast.ClassDef):\n                                                # For classes, append to body\n                                                node.body.extend(self.new_nodes)\n                                            else:\n                                                # For functions, need to handle indentation\n                                                for new_node in self.new_nodes:\n                                                    node.body.append(new_node)\n                                    return node"
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                }
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               }
