                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "content": "Looking at the debug output, I see we have two main issues to fix:\n\n1. Comments are being lost when we parse the AST:\n```python\nDEBUG - New source:\ndef my_func():\n    # First comment\n    x = 1\n    # Target comment\n    z = 3\n    y = 2\n\n# But result is:\ndef my_func():\n    x = 1\n    z = 3\n    y = 2\n```\n\n2. One-line function handling is creating invalid indentation:\n```python\nDEBUG - New source:\n    def method(self): pass\n        pass\n        x = 1\n```\n\nLet's fix the one-line function handling first by modifying how we handle these special cases:",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "pending_results": [],
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "role": "assistant",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "tool_calls": [
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               {
