                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  "content": "Looking at the debug output, I see we have an indentation issue when reconstructing the source. We're keeping the original indentation in the source which is causing parse errors:\n\n```python\nDEBUG - Original source:\n    def another_method(self):  # <-- Has leading indentation\n        # Insert here\n        pass\n\nDEBUG - New source:\n    def another_method(self):  # <-- Leading indentation causes parse error\n        # Insert here\n        x = 42\n        pass\nDEBUG - Parse error: unexpected indent (<unknown>, line 1)\n```\n\nLet me modify the _handle_insertion method to properly handle indentation by dedenting the source before parsing:",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  "pending_results": [],
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  "role": "assistant",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  "tool_calls": [
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   {
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    "type": "tool_use",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    "id": "toolu_017whKtvi4JxKRE4JzZY5fF3",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    "name": "add_function_to_class",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    "input": {
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     "file_path": "bots/tools/python_editing_tools.py",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     "class_name": "ScopeTransformer",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     "new_method_def": "\n                                                                            def _normalize_indentation(self, source):\n                                                                                \"\"\"Remove common leading indentation from all lines.\"\"\"\n                                                                                lines = source.split('\\n')\n                                                                                # Find minimum indentation of non-empty lines\n                                                                                indents = [len(line) - len(line.lstrip()) \n                                                                                         for line in lines if line.strip()]\n                                                                                if not indents:\n                                                                                    return source\n                                                                                min_indent = min(indents)\n                                                                                if min_indent == 0:\n                                                                                    return source\n                                                                                # Remove that amount of indentation from all lines\n                                                                                return '\\n'.join(\n                                                                                    line[min_indent:] if line.strip() else ''\n                                                                                    for line in lines\n                                                                                )\n                                                                            \n                                                                            def _handle_insertion(self, node):\n                                                                                \"\"\"Handle inserting nodes after a specific point.\"\"\"\n                                                                                if isinstance(self.insert_after, str) and '::' not in self.insert_after:\n                                                                                    # Line-based insertion\n                                                                                    if isinstance(node, (ast.FunctionDef, ast.AsyncFunctionDef)):\n                                                                                        print(f\"\\nDEBUG - Function node: {node.name}\")\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        # Check for one-line function\n                                                                                        if node.lineno == node.end_lineno:\n                                                                                            line = self.file_lines[node.lineno-1]\n                                                                                            return self._handle_one_line_function(node, line)\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        # Get original source with comments\n                                                                                        orig_source = self._preserve_node_source(node)\n                                                                                        print(f\"DEBUG - Original source:\\n{orig_source}\")\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        # Normalize indentation\n                                                                                        norm_source = self._normalize_indentation(orig_source)\n                                                                                        print(f\"DEBUG - Normalized source:\\n{norm_source}\")\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        # Split into def line and body\n                                                                                        lines = norm_source.split('\\n')\n                                                                                        def_line = lines[0]\n                                                                                        body_lines = lines[1:]\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        # Find the line and its indentation\n                                                                                        target = self.insert_after.strip()\n                                                                                        print(f\"DEBUG - Looking for target: '{target}'\")\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        for i, line in enumerate(body_lines):\n                                                                                            line = line.rstrip()\n                                                                                            print(f\"DEBUG - Checking line: '{line}'\")\n                                                                                            if line.strip() == target:\n                                                                                                print(f\"DEBUG - Found match at line {i}\")\n                                                                                                self.line_match_count += 1\n                                                                                                if self.line_match_count == 1:\n                                                                                                    # Insert new nodes with proper indentation\n                                                                                                    insertion = []\n                                                                                                    for new_node in self.new_nodes:\n                                                                                                        node_lines = _py_ast_to_source(new_node).split('\\n')\n                                                                                                        for nl in node_lines:\n                                                                                                            if nl.strip():\n                                                                                                                insertion.append('    ' + nl.lstrip())\n                                                                                                            else:\n                                                                                                                insertion.append('')\n                                                                                                    print(f\"DEBUG - Insertion lines: {insertion}\")\n                                                                                                    \n                                                                                                    # Insert after the matching line\n                                                                                                    body_lines[i:i+1] = [body_lines[i]] + insertion\n                                                                                                    self.success = True\n                                                                                                    break\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        if self.line_match_count == 0:\n                                                                                            print(\"DEBUG - No matches found\")\n                                                                                            return node\n                                                                                        elif self.line_match_count > 1:\n                                                                                            raise ValueError(f\"Ambiguous insert_after - found {self.line_match_count} matches for: {self.insert_after}\")\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        # Reconstruct the function preserving comments\n                                                                                        new_source = def_line + '\\n' + '\\n'.join(l for l in body_lines if l is not None)\n                                                                                        print(f\"DEBUG - New source:\\n{new_source}\")\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        try:\n                                                                                            # Parse the normalized source\n                                                                                            new_node = ast.parse(new_source).body[0]\n                                                                                            \n                                                                                            # Copy over original node attributes\n                                                                                            for attr in ['lineno', 'col_offset', 'end_lineno', 'end_col_offset']:\n                                                                                                if hasattr(node, attr):\n                                                                                                    setattr(new_node, attr, getattr(node, attr))\n                                                                                            \n                                                                                            # Store the original source in the node for later use\n                                                                                            new_node._source = orig_source\n                                                                                            return new_node\n                                                                                        except Exception as e:\n                                                                                            print(f\"DEBUG - Parse error: {str(e)}\")\n                                                                                            return node\n                                                                                    return node\n                                                                                else:\n                                                                                    # Scope-based insertion\n                                                                                    if self.insert_after:\n                                                                                        target_path = self.insert_after.split('::')\n                                                                                        current_path = self.current_path\n                                                                                        print(f\"DEBUG - Scope insertion: target={target_path}, current={current_path}\")\n                                                                                        \n                                                                                        # Check if we're at the target scope\n                                                                                        if target_path == current_path:\n                                                                                            self.success = True\n                                                                                            if isinstance(node, ast.ClassDef):\n                                                                                                # For classes, append to body\n                                                                                                node.body.extend(self.new_nodes)\n                                                                                            else:\n                                                                                                # For functions, need to handle indentation\n                                                                                                for new_node in self.new_nodes:\n                                                                                                    node.body.append(new_node)\n                                                                                    return node"
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    }
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   }
