                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             "command": "\n            echo \"WORK ORDER: Python Code Editor Refactoring\n            \n            FILES:\n            - Main implementation: bots/tools/python_editing_tools.py\n            - Test suite: tests/test_python_edit.py\n            \n            CURRENT STATUS:\n            - 13 tests passing, 8 failing\n            - Recently modified import handling in python_edit function\n            - Using pytest-style scope syntax (file.py::class::method)\n            \n            REMAINING ISSUES:\n            1. Comment Preservation:\n               - Comments are being lost when parsing/reconstructing AST\n               - Debug output shows comments in original source but not in final output\n               - Affects both inline and block comments\n            \n            2. Import Handling:\n               - Import statements need to be collected and placed at top of file\n               - Must handle multi-line parenthesized imports\n               - Need to maintain order: new imports, existing imports, then code\n            \n            3. Indentation:\n               - Nested scopes losing proper indentation\n               - Need to preserve indentation in class methods and nested functions\n            \n            EDGE CASES TO HANDLE:\n            1. One-line function definitions (def func(): pass)\n            2. Async functions\n            3. Decorated methods\n            4. Nested classes and functions\n            5. Empty files\n            6. Comments and docstrings\n            7. Multi-line imports with parentheses\n            8. File start insertion with __FILE_START__ token\n            \n            GRAMMAR SPECIFICATION:\n            scope ::= file_path \"::\" path?\n            file_path ::= [^:]+ \".py\"  # Any non-colon chars ending in .py\n            path ::= element (\"::\" element)*  # Chain of classes/functions\n            element ::= [A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*  # Python identifier rules\n            \n            INSERTION MODES:\n            1. Replace at scope\n            2. Insert after line match\n            3. Insert after scope\n            4. Insert at file start\n            \n            TEST CATEGORIES:\n            1. Basic functionality (file level, class, method)\n            2. Nested scopes (class in class, function in function)\n            3. Comment preservation\n            4. Import handling\n            5. Indentation preservation\n            6. Error cases (invalid scope, ambiguous insert)\n            \n            NEXT STEPS:\n            1. Fix comment preservation in ScopeTransformer\n            2. Verify import handling changes\n            3. Fix indentation in nested scopes\n            4. Add more test cases for edge cases\n            \n            NOTES:\n            - Use _clean() for code cleaning/dedenting\n            - Use _py_ast_to_source() for AST to source conversion\n            - Handle all errors via _process_error()\n            - Maintain same error handling pattern as other tools\" > work_order.txt"
