                                                                                             {
                                                                                              "content": "The tests reveal a specific issue with file start insertion:\n\n1. Works correctly when file is empty\n2. Works correctly when file has no imports\n3. Fails when file has existing imports\n\nLooking at the debug output:\n```\nDEBUG - File lines: ['import os\\n', 'from typing import List\\n', 'import sys\\n', 'x = 1']\n```\n\nThe problem is in how we're handling `__FILE_START__`. In the code:\n```python\nif insert_after == '__FILE_START__':\n    tree.body = existing_imports + import_nodes + code_nodes + non_imports\n```\n\nWe're appending the new imports after existing imports, but `__FILE_START__` should mean \"at the very start of the file\". Let me write one more test to confirm this understanding:",
