                                            "node_class": "AnthropicNode",
                                            "replies": [
                                             {
                                              "content": "Let me analyze how the old tool (python_editing_tools.py) handled these issues:\n\n1. Comment/String Handling:\n- The old tool also used `_py_ast_to_source` and accepted the quote standardization\n- It didn't try to preserve comments except in very specific cases:\n  - In `_handle_insertion`, it preserved comments by working with the raw file lines for the specific function being modified\n  - This was a hybrid approach: AST for structure, raw lines for preservation\n\n2. Indentation:\n- The old tool handled indentation by:\n  - Measuring exact indentation from source lines: `current_indent = len(line) - len(line.lstrip())`\n  - Applying that exact indentation to new lines: `' ' * current_indent + nl.lstrip()`\n- This worked well for line-based insertions but was less perfect for full node replacements\n\nFor the new tool, I see a few possible approaches:\n\n1. Token-based approach:\n```python\ndef _preserve_source(source, node):\n    \"\"\"Replace node's content with a unique token, then restore after AST operations\"\"\"\n    token = f\"__SOURCE_PRESERVE_{id(node)}__\"\n    preserved_text = source[node.lineno-1:node.end_lineno]\n    return token, preserved_text\n\ndef _restore_source(source, tokens):\n    \"\"\"Restore preserved source text from tokens\"\"\"\n    for token, text in tokens.items():\n        source = source.replace(token, text)\n    return source\n```\n\n2. Hybrid approach (like the old tool):\n```python\ndef _handle_node(node, source_lines):\n    \"\"\"Use AST for structure but source_lines for exact text\"\"\"\n    if hasattr(node, 'lineno'):\n        original_text = '\\n'.join(source_lines[node.lineno-1:node.end_lineno])\n        return original_text\n    return _py_ast_to_source(node)\n```\n\n3. Full source mapping:\n```python\nclass SourceMapper:\n    \"\"\"Map AST nodes to their exact source representation\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, source):\n        self.source = source\n        self.line_starts = [0] + [m.start() for m in re.finditer('\\n', source)]\n    \n    def get_exact_source(self, node):\n        \"\"\"Get exact source including comments and formatting\"\"\"\n        start = self.line_starts[node.lineno-1] + node.col_offset\n        end = self.line_starts[node.end_lineno-1] + node.end_col_offset\n        return self.source[start:end]\n```\n\nMy recommendation would be:\n1. For the immediate fix: Use the hybrid approach like the old tool - it's proven to work\n2. For a better solution: Implement the SourceMapper approach - it's more robust and maintainable\n3. Accept some standardization (like quote types) as a reasonable tradeoff\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these approaches or suggest others?",
