                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     {
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      "content": "Thanks! We've successfully:\n\n1. Simplified the token format to `\u00abTOKEN__hash_index\u00bb`\n2. Preserved exact whitespace and formatting\n3. Made the tokenization/detokenization round-trip work perfectly\n4. Removed the need for executable Python tokens\n\nThe key insights that helped:\n1. Using special characters (\u00ab \u00bb) that won't appear in normal Python code\n2. Preserving exact whitespace around comments by using string positions\n3. Focusing on perfect round-trip preservation rather than executable tokens\n4. Handling multiline strings and comments separately\n\nWould you like me to:\n1. Add more test cases for edge cases?\n2. Update the docstrings to reflect the new approach?\n3. Start integrating this with the main python_edit function?\n4. Something else?",
