                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         {
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          "content": "Ah, you raise a crucial point! Our tokens with \u00ab \u00bb characters won't be valid Python syntax, which means:\n\n1. The AST parser won't be able to parse the tokenized code\n2. This breaks the core functionality of python_edit which relies on AST manipulation\n3. We need tokens that are both:\n   - Valid Python syntax (for AST)\n   - Uniquely identifiable (for replacement)\n\nWe had the right idea about preserving formatting, but we need tokens that work with Python's AST. Maybe we should:\n\n1. Use valid Python identifiers for tokens in the AST-processed code\n2. Keep track of the exact original formatting separately\n3. Apply the formatting preservation during the final detokenization\n\nOr would you suggest a different approach? How should we balance:\n- AST compatibility\n- Exact formatting preservation\n- Reliable token identification",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          "pending_results": [],
