                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             {
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "content": "Ah, that's a clever solution! Using `;;;` has several advantages:\n\n1. It's valid Python syntax (multiple statements can be separated by semicolons)\n2. It's extremely unlikely to appear in real code\n3. It's easier to type/read than special characters\n4. Most importantly - it won't interfere with AST parsing!\n\nThe issues we had before with semicolons were:\n1. Single `;` was ambiguous because it's commonly used in Python\n2. Double `;;` wasn't distinct enough\n3. We were trying to make the tokens be valid Python expressions/statements, which complicated things\n\nLet me modify the token format to use `;;;TOKEN__hash_index;;;`. This should:\n- Be valid Python syntax\n- Be very distinct and searchable\n- Work with AST parsing\n- Be easy to replace during detokenization\n\nWould you like me to update the functions with this new format?",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              "pending_results": [],
